race.comment: INTERJECTION (2) is back after a five-month spell. The highlight last prep was a barnstorming third, beaten just half a length, in the Listed South Pacific over 1400m at Randwick. Trialling well and has the class to take this out. THEBLADE (8) stalked the pace and had his chance but found one better over 1200m at Warwick Farm last start. Starting to test the patience but out to this trip at the fourth run back looks ideal. MIRRA IMPACT (3) last appeared when an easy winner over 1400m at Hawkesbury nine weeks ago. Good fresh performer who tackles a better race today but is not out of the equation. ZOUNAKA (11) battled on well and was only 1.6 lengths behind subsequent winner Oakfield Jupiter over 1200m at Randwick recently. Needs this trip now and draws the fence so plenty of ticks. FLEETING SPIRIT (14) comes under notice off a five-week let-up with blinkers going on for the first time.
